Product name: Sympathy Gift Basket (small); Bereavement Gift;Grief Care; In Memory of Gift; Comfort Gift; Thinking of you Gift; Funeral gifft; Condolences
Description:
Often times during tragedy and after loss, words feel so insignificant. When we see a friend or loved one hurting we want to do something but we're just not sure what that something is. When words fall short, let a Sympathy Gift Basket do the talking for you. As a result of experiencing grief first hand, we have made it our mission to put together care baskets full of handmade mementos and hand-picked items to send comfort to a loved one who has  just embarked on the journey of grief after losing a loved one. The personalized items are a beautiful way to honor and memorialize their lost loved one. Although there is often nothing we can do to fix a tragic situation, we can offer support to make the journey of a grieving friend just a little bit easier. Sending a Sympathy Gift Basket is a tangible way to show someone how much you truly care.
The small grief basket contains the following 7 items: 
1. A 5x7 hand-lettered print* - (when framed can serve as an encouragement or if Scripture is chosen as a reminder that God is near and knows right where your loved one is.) 
2. All natural homemade lip balm - (an essential to restore chapped lips as a result of the countless tears that will fall. Made with organic coconut oil, shea butter, beeswax, and spearmint oil)
3. Handmade Lavender soap
4. A remembrance candle - (a candle to light in remembrance of the lost loved one's DOB, anniversary, or DOD)
5. A small handpicked journal** - (Just as David poured out his heart in the Psalms, writing can be very therapeutic as your loved one walks through grief.)
6. A hand-lettered wooden ornament with the lost loved one's name* - (something your grieving friend can hang in their home or office to represent their lost loved one)
7. Package of forget-me-not seeds in a hand-lettered envelope - (These flowers germinate very easily and take over more ground each year to serve as an even greater reminder as time goes on)
*PLEASE INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING IN 'NOTE TO SELLER' AT CHECKOUT:
1. The Psalm 56:8 print shown in the listing photos will be included in your basket unless you indicate that you'd like us to send you pictures of other options in an Etsy Conversation.
2. The name and/or dates you'd like to have personalized on the wooden ornament. If you'd prefer not to have the name and date, we can do a short phrase such as "It is well" or a word such as "hope" or "love."
3. What you would like the to/from gift tag to say that is attached to the twine wrapped around the basket?
**We will send you a photo in an Etsy conversation of the journals we have available to choose from.
We would love to hear about the person you are purchasing a basket for. We'd be honored to hear their story and be a small part of their journey. Send us an Etsy conversation with any information you'd like to share and we will keep it in mind as we select the handpicked items.
Please note that basket colors and materials vary.

Product name: Wooden Double-Sided Hand-Painted Aggravation Board Game, Solid Oak-Wood
Description: Hand-Painted Oak Aggravation Game Board. Sit down with the family and enjoy a classic game of Aggravation (also called Wahoo). The Aggravation board is hand-crafted out of solid wood by Mennonite folks in Holmes County, Ohio. The hexagon board is then meticulously hand painted by Kyle. The result is a beautiful Aggravation Game Board meant to last generations of play. It is double sided so you can play with up to 6 players on the one side and with up to 4 players on the other side. To play, move your marble players around the board according to the roll of your dice and try to position your marbles in the home positions before your opponents do. You can send your opponent's players back by landing on a location that they occupy, thus making them "aggravated". Choose between the economical 16" wide board, the popular 20"wide board, or the large 24" wide Board. These dimensions are the width across the points of the hexagon board which is the widest point. The Aggravation Game Board, 24 Playing Marbles and 6 Dice in a Drawstring Carry Bag, and Instructions for Play are all included. Note: Because this item is handmade, the wood grain pattern and coloration may be slightly different than pictured.

Product name: Silver feather ring Sterling silver ring Turquoise ring Bohemian ring Gypsy ring Hippie ring 925 silver ring Gift for her Mothers day gift
Description:
Classic silver feather ring handcrafted by Tibetan artisan. Tibetan Jewellery is also known as Buddhist jewellery or Himalayan jewellery. Jewellery plays an important role in the culture of Tibet. Jewellery is a part of dress, a symbol of spirituality, and a part of everyday life. This area of the world is predominantly Buddhist. The wearing of jewellery is a way to draw close to the gods. Jewellery also has the properties of an amulet, bring protection from evil spirits to the wearer. 
Feather has long held many meanings for many cultures. Most tribal wisdom relate to the feather as an embodiment of bird spirit. 
Material: Sterling silver and Turquoise
Turquoise symbolizes the sky and the sea and because the sky is endless the turquoise stone represents infinity, or the limitless ascension of the mind. 
Size: Adjustable, Best fit US ring size 6-8 (UK: L1/2 – P1/2), can adjust to other sizes, Width: 1.3cm(0.5") 
*PACKAGING*
This ring will come with a quality jewellery box in natural colour and ready to give as a gift. 
*SHIPPING INFORMATION*
UNITED KINGDOM
I use First Class Royal Mail for deliveries within the UK. According to Royal Mail, delivery aim is 1-3 working days. For additional security you can add First Class Signed shipping upgrade at checkout.
ALL OTHER COUNTRIES
I use International standard Air Mail to all the European countries, plus Australia, Canada, Japan, New Zealand, Russia and United States. There is NO TRACKING NUMBER with this service. Please add the International Tracked and Signed shipping upgrade at checkout if you need additional security.
For the rest of the countries in the world, I only use International Tracked and (or) Signed shipping. The standard shipping for these countries are Tracked and (or) Signed. 
According to Royal Mail, for European Countries delivery aim is 3-7 working days. For the countries outside of Europe, delivery aim is 5-10 working days. Please note the above are Royal Mail aimed delivery times. Weather conditions, custom control and other unexpected factors might delay shipping. 
*RETURNS & EXCHANGES*
I really hope you are fully satisfied with your purchase, but if for any reason you are not please contact me first via Etsy conversations. I will do my best to resolve any issues as I believe all the issues can be resoled in a positive way. Returns and Exchanges will be happily accepted. Just contact me within 14 days of delivery.

Product name: Hammered Hoop Earrings for Gauged Ears. Nahusha Tribal Hoops. Threaders. Made To Order.
Description:
The Nahusha Hoops are inspired by my ouroboros Anglo Saxon brooches. Designed in lightweight, work-hardened aluminium to be worn through tunnels. The tumbled and hammered aluminium takes on a moon-glow. Perfect to wear if you don't want to stretch your gauge further but still want a minimalist rustic statement earring; they look heavy but are actually light to wear. This abstracted hoop is inspired by the World Serpents known throughout world myth as a creator-destroyer and keeper of secrets.
I make these hoops in 2 gauge sizes: large 4g (4.50 mm) weighing about 5 grams each; and medium 6g (3.25mm) weighing 2 grams each. All hoops measure approximately 2" in diameter.
Open hoop by gently pulling one end toward you and then sliding it back into place, like a jump ring. 
Known to the Gnostics as the Wise Serpent, the Ouroboros revealed the mysteries of the heavens, protecting the world-egg, this symbol can be traced back to an earlier Goddess, Nehushta, a parallel of the Hindu world-serpent Nahusha. The Norse called this the Nidhogg, the World Serpent eating away at the roots of the World Tree.  A wingless dragon, she took on a darker significance in the Middle Ages when female snakes were thought to swallow the male in order to reproduce.
Here's what one satisfied customer had to say about these hoops:
"Perfect weight to them. Love the hammered texture. Easy to wear and goes with a lot of shit. Thank you again. Will be ordering new earrings soon" - Kali
